15 contract. Such renewal is effective unless the consumer or small business gives notice
16 to the seller of the consumer's or small business's intention to terminate the service
17 contract.
18 (2) 'Consumer' means a natural person or a nonprofit organization exempt from taxation
19 under Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 receiving service,
20 maintenance, or repair benefits under a service contract. The term does not include a
21 natural person engaged in business or employed by or otherwise acting on behalf of a
22 governmental entity if the person enters into the service contract as part of or ancillary
23 to the person's business activities or on behalf of the business or governmental entity.
24 (3) 'Seller' means any person, firm, partnership, association, or corporation engaged in
25 commerce that sells, leases, or offers to sell or lease any service to a consumer or small
26 business pursuant to a service contract.
27 (4) 'Service contract' means a written contract for the performance of services for a
28 specified period of time.
29 (5) 'Small business' means a business that is independently owned and operated, is not
30 dominant in its field of operation, and employs fewer than 200 employees.
31 13-12-2.
32 Any seller that sells, leases, or offers to sell or lease any service to a consumer or small
33 business pursuant to a service contract that has an automatic renewal provision shall
34 disclose the automatic renewal provision clearly and conspicuously in the contract or
35 contract offer.
36 13-12-3.
37 (a) Any seller that sells, leases, or offers to sell or lease any service to a consumer or small
38 business pursuant to a service contract for a specified period of 12 months or more and that
39 automatically renews for a specified period of more than one month, unless the consumer
