40 or small business cancels the contract, shall provide the consumer or small business with
41 written or electronic notification of the automatic renewal provision. Notification shall be
42 provided to the consumer or small business no less than 30 days or no more than 60 days
43 before the cancellation deadline pursuant to the automatic renewal provision. Such
44 notification shall disclose clearly and conspicuously:
45 (1) That unless the consumer or small business cancels the contract, the contract will
46 automatically renew; and
47 (2) The methods by which the consumer or small business may obtain details of the
48 automatic renewal provision and cancellation procedure, including contacting the seller
49 at a specified telephone number or address, referring to the contract, or any other method.
50 (b) For any contract for service to a consumer or small business that automatically renews
51 for a specified period of more than 24 months, the seller shall, in addition to providing the
52 notification required under subsection (a) of this Code section, obtain the following for the
53 automatic renewal provision of such contract to be enforceable:
54 (1) Written or electronic acknowledgment from the consumer or small business of
55 receipt of the notification required under subsection (a) of this Code section; and
56 (2) An affirmative written or electronic response that the consumer or small business
57 does not intend to terminate the service contract.
58 13-12-4.
59 This chapter shall not apply to:
60 (1) A financial institution as provided in Chapter 1 or 2 of Title 7 or any depository
61 institution as defined in 12 U.S.C. Section 1813(c)(2);
62 (2) A foreign bank maintaining a branch or agency licensed under the laws of any state
63 of the United States;
64 (3) Any subsidiary or affiliate of an entity provided in paragraph (1) or (2) of this Code
65 section;
